9/14 Lecture notes

Project managers are hated because they have to nag the other engineers.
There are free project management softwares - Project Libre
 - However, its probably easier to just set up some excel tables to keep track of management

Basic steps in project managment:
 1. Define project: Ddeliverables, specifications, completion criteria
 2. generate tasks: > Deliverables, Milestones
                  > Work Breakdown structure 
 3. determine roles responsibilities: Who owns what, subject matter experts, by dicipline etc
 4. determine task sequence/critical path: Predecessor tasks, parallel tasks, estimate duration of tasks
 5. develop schedule: start at end date and work backwards
                  > early start dates, latest start dates, and early/ late end dates
                  > Save ALL slack time for April
 6. determine resource availabilty: Balance workloads and responsibilies according to availability of resources
 7. stablish budget: after everything is mapped out, then we can add costs up
 8. analyze risks and contigency plans: likely things that would prevent the project from succeeding -> prevention, mitigation 
 9. track and manage project: weekly updates, track effort/timeline, shift resources if necessary
 10. post project review: Good bad and ugly




